    <h2>U.S. Supreme Court</h2>
    <h1>United State v. Barker, 15 U.S. 395 (1817)</h1>
    <h2>United State v. Barker</h2>
    <h2>15 U.S. (2 Wheat.) 395</h2>
    <h2>Syllabus</h2>
    <p>A writ of error does not lie to carry to this Court a civil cause which has been carried from the district to the circuit court by writ of error.</p>
    <p>The United States never pays costs.</p>
    <p>MR. CHIEF JUSTICE MARSHALL.</p>
    <p>The United States never pays costs.</p>
    <p>Writ of error dismissed without costs.</p>
  </opinion>
